# Native interactions & mutations

## Pressable must be honest

- Every `Pressable` with `accessibilityRole="button"` needs a working `onPress`, or remove/hide it.
- When `disabled={...}`, also set:
  - `accessibilityState={{ disabled: isDisabled }}`
  - visual feedback: `disabled:opacity-40` or `disabled:opacity-50` on `className`
  - muted icon color when disabled (e.g. `useThemeColor("muted-foreground")`)

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — disabled prop only, still looks clickable
<Pressable disabled={!entry} onPress={handleMenu}>

// ✅ GOOD
const isDisabled = entry == null;
<Pressable
  disabled={isDisabled}
  accessibilityState={{ disabled: isDisabled }}
  className="... active:opacity-70 disabled:opacity-40"
>
  <Ionicons color={isDisabled ? mutedForeground : accentForeground} />
</Pressable>
```

## Mutation feedback — toast, not Alert

- Use `useMutationToast()` from `@/lib/mutation-toast` for mutation success/failure.
- `mutationToast.error(err, "Fallback message")` — pass raw `err`, not pre-parsed string.
- `mutationToast.success("...")` on success before navigation.
- Keep `Alert.alert` only for permission/settings flows, not mutation results.

## Error extraction

- Import `messageFromError` from `@/lib/error-utils` when Alert is still required.
- Do not copy-paste `messageFromError` into screen files.

## Double-submit guard

`disabled={submitting}` alone is not enough — rerender is async. Block re-entry synchronously:

```tsx
const isSubmittingRef = useRef(false);

const handleSubmit = async () => {
  if (isSubmittingRef.current) return;
  // validation...
  isSubmittingRef.current = true;
  setSubmitting(true);
  try { /* upload + mutation */ }
  finally {
    isSubmittingRef.current = false;
    setSubmitting(false);
  }
};
```

## Spinner / icon colors

- Use `useThemeColor("primary-foreground")` (or `accent-foreground`) for `ActivityIndicator`.
- Never hardcode `#ffffff` or hex in native components.
